data.title: Willem van de Velde II (Leiden 1633-1707 Greenwich)
meta_keywords: Willem van de Velde II (Leiden 1633-1707 Greenwich)
data.meta_description: Willem van de Velde II (Leiden 1633-1707 Greenwich) Shipping on a calm sea  black chalk, pen and grey ink, grey wash, pen and black ink framing lines, fragmentary watermark Foolscap 4 3 ⁄ 4 x 7 1 ⁄ 2 in. (12 x 19 cm)
data.text:
The condition of lots can vary widely and the nature of the lots sold means that they are unlikely to be in a perfect condition. Lots are sold in the condition they are in at the time of sale.

Executed on laid paper and fully laid down. The sheet appears to have been cleaned and there is a vertical crease in the left half of the sheet. There is a further crease in the lower right and there is a dent in the lower right. There are some further minor foxmarks. The media have faded. Framed.

Print Report
